<% content_for(:page_title) { "Cookie Policy — CrewControl" } %>
<% content_for(:page_description) { "Information about how CrewControl uses cookies and similar technologies." } %>

<section class="legal-page">
  <div class="marketing-container">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: <%= Date.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %></p>

    <div class="legal-content">
      <h2>1. What Are Cookies</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the site function correctly and remember your preferences.</p>

      <h2>2. Cookies We Use</h2>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>Required for the service to function. These include your session token (to keep you signed in) and CSRF protection tokens. These cannot be disabled.</p>

      <h3>Preference Cookies</h3>
      <p>Store your chosen theme (dark/light mode). These improve your experience but are not strictly necessary.</p>

      <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
      <p>We may use analytics cookies to understand how visitors interact with the site. These are anonymised and help us improve the service.</p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>Our payment provider (Stripe) may set cookies during the checkout process. These are governed by Stripe's own cookie policy.</p>

      <h2>4. Managing Cookies</h2>
      <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling essential cookies may prevent the service from functioning correctly.</p>

      <h2>5. Contact</h2>
      <p>For questions about our use of cookies, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@crew-control.io">support@crew-control.io</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
